  "runningCoachInsightBounceTitle": "Bounce",
  "runningCoachBounceGoodSummary": "Your vertical movement looks controlled, which helps keep energy moving forward.",
  "runningCoachBounceGoodCue": "Keep pushing backward into the ground instead of bouncing upward.",
  "runningCoachBounceGoodDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20m ankle dribbles before your next sprint set.",
  "runningCoachBounceHighSummary": "There is extra up-and-down bounce in the clip, which can waste energy.",
  "runningCoachBounceHighCue": "Think quick contacts and push the ground behind you, not straight down.",
  "runningCoachBounceHighDrill": "Drill: 3 x 20m ankle dribbles and straight-leg runs with short contacts.",
  "runningCoachInsightFootStrikeTitle": "Foot strike",
  "runningCoachFootStrikeGoodSummary": "The lead foot is landing close enough to the hips that the step can keep rolling forward.",
  "runningCoachFootStrikeGoodCue": "Keep landing under the hips and let speed come from push-off, not reaching.",
  "runningCoachFootStrikeGoodDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20m wicket-style runs with short, quick contacts.",
  "runningCoachFootStrikeOverSummary": "The lead foot is reaching too far in front of the hips, which can create braking at contact.",
  "runningCoachFootStrikeOverCue": "Bring the landing point back under the hips and think push back, not reach forward.",
  "runningCoachFootStrikeOverDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20m A-march plus 2 x 20m wicket-style runs with shorter contacts.",
  "runningCoachInsightKneeTitle": "Knee flexion",
  "runningCoachKneeGoodSummary": "The support knee is bending enough to stay springy without collapsing.",
  "runningCoachKneeGoodCue": "Keep the stance leg soft and reactive instead of locking on landing.",
  "runningCoachKneeGoodDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20m pogo runs, then 2 x 20m dribble runs.",
  "runningCoachKneeStraightSummary": "The support knee is landing too straight, which can make the step look stiff and heavy.",
  "runningCoachKneeStraightCue": "Soften the landing knee and let the leg accept the ground under the hips.",
  "runningCoachKneeStraightDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20m dribble runs with bent-knee contacts and quick steps.",
  "runningCoachKneeCollapseSummary": "The support knee is folding too much after contact, so the stance leg is losing stiffness.",
  "runningCoachKneeCollapseCue": "Stay springy through the stance leg and keep the hips stacked over the foot.",
  "runningCoachKneeCollapseDrill": "Drill: 2 x 15m single-leg pogo hops per side, then 2 x 20m dribble runs.",
  "runningCoachInsightArmTitle": "Arm carriage",
  "runningCoachArmGoodSummary": "Your elbows stay in a compact range that supports rhythm without over-tensing the upper body.",
  "runningCoachArmGoodCue": "Keep the elbows bent and let the hands travel front to back with the same rhythm as the legs.",
  "runningCoachArmGoodDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20s wall arm switches, then 2 x 20m arm-drive marches.",
  "runningCoachArmOpenSummary": "Your elbows are opening too much, so the arms may be leaking rhythm instead of helping it.",
  "runningCoachArmOpenCue": "Keep the elbows more bent and drive the hands back past the hips instead of reaching long.",
  "runningCoachArmOpenDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20s wall arm switches while holding a compact 80-100 degree elbow bend.",
  "runningCoachArmTightSummary": "Your elbows are staying too tight, which can shorten the arm swing and make the stride feel forced.",
  "runningCoachArmTightCue": "Relax the shoulders and let the elbows open a little more while the hands keep moving backward.",
  "runningCoachArmTightDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20m marching arm swings with relaxed shoulders and a smoother back drive.",
  "runningCoachInsightStrideTitle": "Stride reach",
  "runningCoachStrideGoodSummary": "Your front foot stays close to a useful landing window under the body.",
  "runningCoachStrideGoodCue": "Keep the same timing and let the stride open from force, not from reaching.",
  "runningCoachStrideGoodDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20m wicket-style quick step runs to keep the same rhythm.",
  "runningCoachStrideShortSummary": "Your stride reach looks short, so you may be holding back and not opening the run enough.",
  "runningCoachStrideShortCue": "Drive the knee forward and let the step open naturally behind a faster arm rhythm.",
  "runningCoachStrideShortDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20m A-march into A-skip to build front-side mechanics.",
  "runningCoachStrideOverSummary": "The front foot is reaching too far ahead of the body, which can create braking.",
  "runningCoachStrideOverCue": "Land closer under the hips and let speed come from push-off, not reaching.",
  "runningCoachStrideOverDrill": "Drill: 2 x 20m A-march and 2 x 20m wicket-style runs with short contacts.",
